This is a Gun Game map made for up to 40 people. There are buyzones at spawn for both teams. 

When you start, you have 3 options of places to go, if you go to one side, you'll end up at a large pool of water with a vehicle at the bottom. Or you could go to the other side which has only vehicles. If you want to go inside the building then you just run straight in. There are stairs right by the door in the building which lead to the second floor and ulitmately the roof. 

This map is relatively quick for gameplay and is excellent for turbo gun game.

With the map file that you can download, I included the .nav file plus screenshots of the map to view before opening it for gameplay.
Un Gun game dinamique !

Extremely compact symmetrical layout coupled with a rather large, asymmetrical visual setting of a building site rooftop. Despite its looks, the map is best suited for small servers. Even though there're 24 spawn points in total, I wouldn't recommend playing this map with more than 16 players on the server.

There're also bottles everywhere, precisely 64 of them, because I had trouble coming up with a name.

Features:
  • 3-story map with endless possibilities to get behind your enemy. In fact, you're guaranteed to accidentally get behind each other regularly. A field day for knife maniacs.
  • Packed playable area and the ability to quickly get to any spot on the map provide for very fast-paced rounds. You don't need DM for this map.
  • Technical pros: The map is very light on resources and is optimized. 3D skybox, radar, soundscapes, cubemaps (both HDR and SDR) and a customized *.nav-file with manually assigned area names - all in one, single 7,5MiB (unpacked size) BSP. Drop it into the /maps and play.
  • Bonus point: Extra effort was taken to ensure that successive spawn points are not near each other. You won't have a whole team spawning in one corner of the map with the rest of the base being completely empty. The map will try to distribute players across the whole base every round. Also it's 2020 so you're expected to keep your distance anyways.

  I made this map in two days. I stayed up all night long making this map and making sure I fixed every bug. 48 hours I spent. Leave comments and suggetions. I even have a story of how you came to the Outpost :) There will be many other Outpost that I will make with more places to go and more secretes to find. And more zombie madness!
<hr>
Story Of the Outpost
<hr>

  It all began with an experimental error when trying to make the perfect super solider. Everything was going well until....until the 
experimental human went all wrong. It changed his skin and then his hunger began to change. He was no longer human. The monster had became something more than human. It became so sort of z zombie looking creature. The monster had killed all the soliders and scientist there. That was 30 years ago.  A war between Terrorist and Counter-Terrorist  have began. A team of 18 Counter-Terrorist have been assigned to go to an outpost called outpost No.1. The Terrorist team has assigned 18 of its soliders to attack the team of 18 Counter-Terrorist. When the CT's have arived to the Outpost No.1 a missile from the Terrorist hit the Ct's plan and the Ct's while going down fired a missile at the T's and both plans landed. When they all came out of the plan there were about to fire at each other but a Howling Screaming sound came out of no where. And down on the street they all looked they saw this monster. They where about to fire until they saw the monster became one of the Ct's and have fired a shot at one of the Ct's solider. It then Jumped into the air and took one of the T's soliders. Over the years the monster has learned how to transform into a human. So together with both Terrorist and Counter-Terrorist they need to bring this monster down before all of them become...Zombies!
<hr>

  Hope that story was good and hope you like the map :)

Zm_zuluville_facility_acp_v1 is a small map that I have created.
My main goal is quite simpile with this map, this is campers must die!
Its not called camping mod after all.

There are a few heavy camping spots but they have a few functions in which zombies can use in order to kill the campers.
Some traps are just buttons on a timer and others you need to know a code to open doors etc.
I also tryed to get rid of most of the corners as a lot of the time zombies can get trapped in this, what I did instead was add 90 degrees arches and what happends is the zombies deflect and end up getting boosted else where, worked well in testing.

The map I know has not a great amount of detail but I wanted all the walls and floor to be smooth and empty so they when the zombies get boosted there is little to get stuck on.

I hope it can be a fun and at times funny map with good balance.

This map is simply a version 2 from my origonal. I spent almost all day today working on the map fixing things such as the lighting, the textures, and adding a bit more to it. I added an entire unground tunnel system and 4 towers which can be accessed from the ground, on top of the buildings, or from underground.

Well in the map there are several rooms that have things such as chairs, couches and vending machines to block the doors with. Although to make these work the best, i'd suggest having ragdoll physics set onto the server, otherwise the map itself won't work as good as it could.

There are also several artillary shooters in the map. There are 2 on one building then one on another. These are fully functional and can be used by pressing 'e' while by them. You can aim them with the wsda buttons and shoot them with the left mouse button (or whatever button you use to fire weapons with).

At the spawns, there are 2 P90 dispencers for each team since a P90 seems like one of the best guns in zombie mod, you can just run up there, grab the gun and run to somewhere safe. 

I put the spawn areas for both teams on opposite sides of the map so the map could be used for other things such as dm instead of only zombie. But both sides have buy zones in them as well.

The map itself is dark in some areas to give it a bit more of a scary feeling to it. Knowing that a zombie could be right behind you, but you can't see it in the dark could ultimately make this map great.

I spent about 38 hours total creating and perfecting this map, so please, if you find problems in it, tell me. I even included a real working ferris wheel to just mess around with and to have fun on (note: i did not make the ferris wheel, it was a downloaded prefab).

I am also working on a deathmatch version of this map which will be made entirely for deathmatch.
